I can't speak to any recent retcons, but here's what I know that was
current as of, say the Millennium series.

<QUOTE PREVIOUSPOST="
&gt; - The histories of the Zamarons and the Star Sapphires
">

The Zamarons have been the female Guardians for a long time.  Dunno if
they were always that, or if it was a retcon early on, but they've been the
distaff branch of the family for decades real-world-time.  The Star Sapphire
was originally given to their queen, who by tradition had to be a
non-Zamaron.  Yep, they outsourced their rulership.  Of course, being
functionally immortal, I suppose it would make sense to give the job to a
mortal to avoid stagnation and complacency.  Carol Ferris was the latest
choice for the job, which came with its own personality graft.
Carol also ended up the host for another entity, the Predator, a male
hunter sort.  In one of the weirder events of the 1990s, the Predator got
Star Sapphire pregnant and they had a kid.  I forget what happened to the
kid, and I expect everyone at DC has as well.

<QUOTE PREVIOUSPOST="
&gt; - What they've been trying to accomplish, and what they're trying to
&gt;accomplish now
">

For the most part, they just didn't like the Guardians and looked for
opportunities to mess with the Green Lanterns.  Not on the &quot;destroy them
all!&quot; level (usually), more like an unfriendly rivalry.  Where the Guardians
were fuddy duddy patriarch types, the Zamarons were space-Amazons, with the
attendant &quot;see each other as deluded fools&quot; outlooks.
Eventually, the Guardians and Zamarons reached approachment during
Millennium and went off to engage in cosmic nookie or something.  Then
Parallax happened, but let's not go into that too deeply.  At some point
later on, Ion/Kyle Rayner brought back the Guardians as children, but it
included females, implying that he brought back pre-split Zamarons as Oans.
One Oan girl ended up rapidly aging to adulthood and taking on a rather
Zamaron outlook, but kept her blue skin (Zamarons are caucasoid).  Around
then I drifted away from GL again.

<QUOTE PREVIOUSPOST="
&gt; - What major and/or significant past stories concerning them will
&gt;have to be discarded or heavily retconned
">

Can't say, but if there's supposed to be multiple Star Sapphires and
always have been, your answer is probably &quot;all of them need to be retconned
or discarded.&quot;  The Star Sapphire was their queen, singular and serially
unique.
However, if it's revealed that the SS Corps is a new invention, then it
might not be necesary to retcon very much, if anything.  They'd just have
decided that the SS power set is useful enough to merit handing out to people
other than their queen, or they just figured out how to make more than one.
After all, Sinestro used to be a singleton too, until they figured out how to
make more yellow rings.

Dave Van Domelen, thinks Carol Ferris and Betty Banner should form a
support group.
